@NODE otherway "Usage through CLI/Default"

 @{b}@{fg highlight}CLI Usage@{ub}@{fg text}

 To use s2mPod through CLI, simply place the main program of s2mPod in an
 accessible place, like the C: drawer, and then goto CLI. Then type in
 @{b}s2m@{ub} and the path and name of the anim.

  E.g.   s2mPod Graphics:Animations/Test.anim


 @{b}@{fg highlight}Default Tool Usage@{ub}@{fg text}

 Very simple this one, simply go the icon of an anim, and put in the drawer
 which s2mPod is situated in, and s2mPod, and then save. Then simply click on it,
 and it will come up.

 E.g  C:s2mPod

@ENDNODE

